'''Hasan Minhaj''' (born September 23, 1985) is an [[United States|American]] actor, comedian and correspondent on ''[[The Daily Show]]''.

==Career==
Minhaj attended the [[University of California, Davis]].<ref name=laughspin>{{cite web|url=http://www.laughspin.com/2009/08/24/hasan-minhaj-giving-comedy-the-college-try/|title=Hasan Minhaj: Giving comedy the college try|date=August 24, 2009|first=Daniel|last=Perlman|work=LAUGHSPIN|accessdate=October 11, 2014}}</ref> There, he became interested in [[stand-up comedy]] after seeing [[Chris Rock]]'s ''[[Never Scared]]'', the first stand-up special he watched. He began traveling to [[San Francisco]] to perform.<ref name=audrey>{{cite web|url=http://audreymagazine.com/fall-13-issue-comedian-hasan-minhaj-talks-the-truth-and-failosophy-and-is-definitely-not-related-to-nicki-minhaj/|title=Comedian Hasan Minhaj Talks “The Truth” and “Failosophy” (and Is Definitely Not Related to Nicki Minaj)|first=Paul|last=Nakayama|work=[[Audrey Magazine]]|date=September 9, 2013|accessdate=October 11, 2014}}</ref> In 2008, he won [[Wild 94.9]]'s "Best Comic Standing" competition, which resulted in his working as an [[opening act]] for [[Katt Williams]], [[Pablo Francisco]], and [[Gabriel Iglesias]]. He also worked part-time for [[Ning (website)|Ning]], an experience he used to write comedy.<ref name=laughspin/>

In 2009, Minhaj moved to [[Los Angeles]] to perform on [[NBC]]'s ''Stand-up for Diversity''.<ref name=laughspin/><ref name=audrey/> He was a finalist on the program.<ref name=laughspin/> Minhaj has appeared on ''[[Arrested Development (TV series)|Arrested Development]]'', ''[[Getting On (U.S. TV series)|Getting On]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/daily-show-adds-two-new-correspondents-210372|title=The Daily Show adds two new correspondents|work=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=October 10, 2014|accessdate=October 11, 2014}}</ref> ''[[Chelsea Lately]]'', and ''[[Disaster Date]]''. He was a series regular on ''[[State of Georgia (TV series)|State of Georgia]]''. Through posting on [[YouTube]], he was cast on ''[[Failosophy]]''.<ref name=audrey/> He hosted ''Stand Up Planet'' and ''The Truth with Hasan Minhaj'', a [[web series]].<ref name=ew/> He lists [[Kevin Shea]], [[W. Kamau Bell]], and [[Arj Barker]] as inspirations.<ref name=audrey/>

Minhaj voiced Rabi Ray Rana in the video game ''[[Far Cry 4]]''. On November 19, 2014, Minhaj joined ''[[The Daily Show]]'' as a correspondent.<ref name=ew>{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/10/10/daily-show-adds-hasan-minhaj-trevor-noah/|title='Daily Show' adds Hasan Minhaj and Trevor Noah|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=October 10, 2014|accessdate=October 11, 2014}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Minhaj's parents are from [[Aligarh, Uttar Pradesh|Aligarh]], [[India]]. They immigrated to [[Davis, California]].<ref name=audrey/>

